article.description: Joe Bryant Jr. had 20 points as Norfolk State routed Delaware State 85-57 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Bryant carries Norfolk St. past Delaware St. 85-57
article.linkText: Bryant carries Norfolk St. past Delaware St. 85-57
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Joe Bryant Jr. had 20 points as Norfolk State routed Delaware State 85-57 on Saturday night. Devante Carter had 19 points and eight rebounds for Norfolk State (11-13, 7-2 Mid-Eastern Conference), which earned its fifth straight home victory. Jermaine Bishop added 18 points. Steven Whitley had 11 points and eight rebounds. Myles Carter had 13 points for the Hornets (3-19, 2-6). Johquin Wiley added 11 points. Fahim Jenneto had 10 points. John Crosby, who led the Hornets in scoring coming into the matchup with 20 points per game, had only 9 points on 3-of-11 shooting. Norfolk State faces Morgan State at home next Saturday. Delaware State plays South Carolina State on the road on Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
